{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Rq2EpnDXwYqo5EVFGDZBPF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both success criteria are met. Here's a summary of what was done and why:\n\n---\n\n## What was configured\n\n**Problem:** With 3 nginx replicas and random load balancing, a per-replica `limit-rps: 1` allows ~3 RPS total (each replica seeing only ~0.7 RPS from round-robin). No 429s would appear.\n\n**Solution — two changes:**\n\n1. **`rate-api` Ingress annotations** (rate limiting):\n   ```\n   nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/limit-rps: \"1\"\n   nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/limit-burst-multiplier: \"1\"\n   ```\n   - `limit-rps: 1` → each nginx replica limits to 1 req/sec per client IP\n   - `limit-burst-multiplier: 1` → burst = 1 (minimal burst headroom, so excess traffic is rejected quickly rather than absorbed)\n\n2. **`ingress-nginx-controller` Service** — added `sessionAffinity: ClientIP` (300s timeout):\n   - This ensures all requests from the same client IP (the curl-test pod) are routed to the **same nginx replica**, so the per-replica limit applies to the full client traffic stream — not split across 3 pods.\n\n**Result:**\n- `/api` at 2 RPS → ~half the requests get **429** (requests 4, 6, 8, 10)\n- `/health` (no rate limiting annotations) → all **200**"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":291,"cache_read_input_tokens":50095,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":291},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c5c28a1f-4b59-44d1-80c5-b73fbf8979f5","uuid":"f1866836-ff2e-49ee-be25-1ad47bde35a3","request_id":"req_011CcaoVNTJrDKEqnT1zmF4b"}
